connected right now. Please…

80
00:08:04,866 --> 00:08:07,433
Why isn't he picking up?

81
00:08:11,200 --> 00:08:12,667
I should go to his place again.

82
00:08:12,733 --> 00:08:16,167
You've been going back and forth
plenty of times already.

83
00:08:16,233 --> 00:08:16,966
I'm sure he'll come.

84
00:08:17,066 --> 00:08:18,900
We promised to meet,
but he's not here and

85
00:08:18,966 --> 00:08:20,500
he's not picking up.
Something's not right!

86
00:08:21,633 --> 00:08:24,067
But how will I find him,
unless I know where he is?

87
00:08:24,133 --> 00:08:25,667
I'm sure he has his reason.

88
00:08:25,733 --> 00:08:27,500
Why are you so worried?

89
00:08:40,700 --> 00:08:43,034
The man who bloomed
those flowers for you.

90
00:08:43,100 --> 00:08:45,666
What about losing him, then?

91
00:08:47,366 --> 00:08:49,366
Someone told me
something terrible.

92
00:08:55,266 --> 00:08:56,700
I'm going to find him.

93
00:08:56,766 --> 00:08:57,666
President Jang.

94
00:09:02,933 --> 00:09:05,266
He's not picking up.

95
00:09:18,733 --> 00:09:21,600
- Hello?
- What do we do?

96
00:09:21,666 --> 00:09:23,434
What is it, Yu-na?

97
00:09:23,500 --> 00:09:25,900
I think Mr. Koo is hurt.

98
00:09:27,366 --> 00:09:29,366
What if he's dead?

99
00:09:30,366 --> 00:09:32,234
What?

100
00:09:32,300 --> 00:09:34,267
No. 3 is dead?

101
00:09:34,333 --> 00:09:37,633
It seems he died while he was off to
catch the murderer.

102
00:09:42,633 --> 00:09:45,367
President Jang. President Jang!

103
00:09:45,433 --> 00:09:46,500
What are we to do?

104
00:09:49,466 --> 00:09:51,266
Mr. Koo is dead.

105
00:09:54,833 --> 00:09:55,866
What?

106
00:10:01,866 --> 00:10:04,134
The guests who are here…

107
00:10:04,200 --> 00:10:07,900
Yu-na followed a car to
find their murderer,

108
00:10:07,966 --> 00:10:11,267
but Mr. Koo went in her stead

109
00:10:11,333 --> 00:10:12,966
saying it was dangerous. And now…

110
00:10:19,700 --> 00:10:21,300
Don't talk nonsense.

111
00:10:23,733 --> 00:10:25,567
Why would Koo Chan-sung die?

112
00:10:25,633 --> 00:10:28,200
Yu-na saw the ambulance
take him away.

113
00:11:17,533 --> 00:11:18,833
Tell me clearly.

114
00:11:20,500 --> 00:11:21,666
What happened, exactly?

115
00:11:24,566 --> 00:11:25,900
Stop crying!

116
00:11:34,833 --> 00:11:35,866
Mr. Koo?

117
00:13:10,166 --> 00:13:11,834
Ji Hyun-joong, you little…!

118
00:13:11,900 --> 00:13:15,167
- Come here!
- President Jang. President Jang!

119
00:13:15,233 --> 00:13:16,200
President Jang!

120
00:13:16,966 --> 00:13:18,366
You…

121
00:13:20,733 --> 00:13:23,666
You're not dead. Thank goodness.

122
00:13:45,966 --> 00:13:46,866
Mr. Koo.

123
00:13:50,700 --> 00:13:55,900
You're alive.

124
00:13:55,966 --> 00:13:58,467
We thought you'd come here
as our guest.

125
00:13:58,533 --> 00:14:00,500
What? Guest?

126
00:14:06,533 --> 00:14:08,900
We were told you went in alone to
meet the murderer,

127
00:14:08,966 --> 00:14:11,534
but then you wouldn't pick up
your phone.

128
00:14:11,600 --> 00:14:13,300
And when we heard someone
got hurt, we thought it was you.

129
00:14:14,700 --> 00:14:16,400
I didn't act recklessly,

130
00:14:16,466 --> 00:14:18,934
clearly knowing that
it could get dangerous.

131
00:14:19,000 --> 00:14:21,366
I called a police officer I know
before going in.

132
00:14:22,500 --> 00:14:23,400
Stop right there!

133
00:14:31,533 --> 00:14:33,933
Good work. So who got hurt?

134
00:14:35,033 --> 00:14:36,266
The culprit.

135
00:14:37,500 --> 00:14:40,167
Mr. Seol Ji-won,
you are under arrest

136
00:14:40,233 --> 00:14:41,600
as a suspect of murder.

137
00:14:53,566 --> 00:14:54,666
Put it down.

138
00:15:11,733 --> 00:15:13,434
It wasn't
a life-threatening injury,

139
00:15:13,500 --> 00:15:15,366
so he'll pay for his sin
while he's still alive.

140
00:15:15,966 --> 00:15:17,600
Thank goodness!

141
00:15:17,666 --> 00:15:20,100
We thought you'd come here
as our guest earlier.

142
00:15:20,166 --> 00:15:21,834
I knew it wasn't the case
as soon as he stepped in.

143
00:15:21,900 --> 00:15:24,300
Whatever. You were crying!

144
00:15:24,366 --> 00:15:26,167
I saw you wipe those tears.

145
00:15:26,233 --> 00:15:27,667
It was snot.

146
00:15:27,733 --> 00:15:30,533
You should talk for yourself.
Your legs almost gave out!

147
00:15:34,033 --> 00:15:36,300
I'm sorry to startle you all.

148
00:15:36,366 --> 00:15:39,334
And… thank you for
worrying about me.

149
00:15:39,400 --> 00:15:42,167
You almost stopped our
already stopped hearts.

150
00:15:42,233 --> 00:15:43,734
What a shock, that was.

151
00:15:43,800 --> 00:15:46,600
Now we'll have another wave of
President Jang's hysteria,

152
00:15:46,666 --> 00:15:48,167
so let's brace ourselves for it.

153
00:15:48,233 --> 00:15:49,200
Here.

154
00:15:57,233 --> 00:15:58,266
- We can do this!
- We can do this!

155
00:16:02,333 --> 00:16:03,500
Ms. Jang Man-wol.

156
00:16:07,933 --> 00:16:09,166
Where'd she go?

157
00:16:11,633 --> 00:16:13,300
I brought these, in case

158
00:16:13,366 --> 00:16:15,200
a few bottles wouldn't be enough
to calm her down.

159
00:16:19,633 --> 00:16:22,200
Ms. Jang Man-wol,
where have you been?

160
00:16:23,966 --> 00:16:26,766
- Have you been out shopping?
- Have a seat, Koo Chan-sung.

161
00:16:37,500 --> 00:16:38,934
You were at the pharmacist's?

162
00:16:39,000 --> 00:16:42,900
Yes, because we don't have
a first-aid kit for the living here.

163
00:16:43,666 --> 00:16:45,234
Did you empty the entire place?

164
00:16:45,300 --> 00:16:47,400
I said, sit.

165
00:16:47,466 --> 00:16:48,366
Let me see.

166
00:16:56,966 --> 00:16:58,700
Goodness… look at you.

167
00:17:02,733 --> 00:17:04,833
But which one?

168
00:17:05,733 --> 00:17:07,400
Let's go with the
most expensive one.

169
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:18,800
- Ouch, that hurts.
- Does it sting?

170
00:17:20,233 --> 00:17:21,734
I guess this one's no good.

171
00:17:21,800 --> 00:17:22,733
Let me see.

172
00:17:26,966 --> 00:17:29,167
Hey, this is for hemorrhoids!

173
00:17:29,233 --> 00:17:30,200
Huh?

174
00:17:31,933 --> 00:17:34,766
Sorry. I used something that's for
your ass on your face.

175
00:17:36,733 --> 00:17:37,834
Come here.

176
00:17:37,900 --> 00:17:39,300
It's alright.

177
00:17:39,800 --> 00:17:42,267
If it heals down there, I'm sure
it'll do the same for the face.

178
00:17:42,333 --> 00:17:43,900
You think your butthole and
your face are the same thing?

179
00:17:44,633 --> 00:17:46,266
Give it to me.
Let's try another one.

180
00:17:50,566 --> 00:17:52,334
Were you shocked?

181
00:17:52,400 --> 00:17:54,466
Because you thought
I'd died and come as a guest?

182
00:17:59,666 --> 00:18:02,400
How could you mistake
something like that?

183
00:18:07,333 --> 00:18:08,766
Because I was scared.

184
00:18:12,600 --> 00:18:18,300
I was so frightened, as if
the whole world had gone black.

185
00:18:24,933 --> 00:18:28,533
I'd never got it wrong, even when
I'd lost my cool over money.

186
00:18:29,300 --> 00:18:31,667
You made me a laughing stock.

187
00:18:31,733 --> 00:18:34,234
All my employees were
watching, too…

188
00:18:34,300 --> 00:18:35,833
Ugh, how embarrassing!

189
00:18:38,266 --> 00:18:40,233
Just which is which?

190
00:18:41,933 --> 00:18:43,367
Wait right here.

191
00:18:43,433 --> 00:18:46,366
I'll see if we have a former
pharmacist among our guests.

192
00:18:49,833 --> 00:18:51,700
You had quite a fright, too.

193
00:18:51,766 --> 00:18:53,300
Shouldn't you also have something?

194
00:18:54,000 --> 00:18:56,500
What, do you have anything
that'll calm me down?

195
00:19:07,266 --> 00:19:08,666
It was quite a shock for you,
right?

196
00:19:16,766 --> 00:19:18,233
Are you the pharmacist, or what?

197
00:19:20,966 --> 00:19:22,866
Well, I am supposed to be
taking care of you.

198
00:19:43,233 --> 00:19:45,467
It's when you hold fear
in your heart,

199
00:19:45,533 --> 00:19:47,700
that the flowers start to wilt.

200
00:19:56,966 --> 00:19:58,400
I have good news, too.

201
00:20:00,200 --> 00:20:01,567
Your Yeon-woo…

202
00:20:01,633 --> 00:20:04,400
I mean, Detective Park Young-soo
arrested the culprit.

203
00:20:04,466 --> 00:20:06,400
He'll probably get
a special promotion.

204
00:20:15,000 --> 00:20:18,266
We found all the drugs and
the needles he used for the murder.

205
00:20:19,566 --> 00:20:22,834
It seems he smuggled the drugs
while importing wine.

206
00:20:22,900 --> 00:20:24,900
This must represent that
website, "Hell-lo."

207
00:20:24,966 --> 00:20:26,833
Did you find Seol Ji-won by
searching this site?

208
00:20:27,700 --> 00:20:28,833
To tell you the truth…

209
00:20:30,233 --> 00:20:31,833
There was a tip-off.

210
00:20:34,900 --> 00:20:35,966
Who?

211
00:20:36,866 --> 00:20:38,934
You're the late Ms. Lee Do-yeon?

212
00:20:39,000 --> 00:20:40,800
My husband is not the murderer.

213
00:20:40,866 --> 00:20:42,434
The murderer is still here.

214
00:20:42,500 --> 00:20:44,267
You shouldn't be prank-calling.

215
00:20:44,333 --> 00:20:47,200
Blood… there's blood.

216
00:20:47,266 --> 00:20:49,267
He draws blood from the dead
and keeps a collection.

217
00:20:49,333 --> 00:20:51,466
Please come here, quick!
It's getting dangerous.

218
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:54,567
We never made it public that
there were traces of

219
00:20:54,633 --> 00:20:56,633
blood being drawn from
the victims' bodies.

220
00:20:57,533 --> 00:20:59,500
That bothered me,
so I came here, and…

221
00:21:00,800 --> 00:21:02,867
There really is blood, right here.

222
00:21:02,933 --> 00:21:04,966
That guy's truly a devil!

223
00:21:06,033 --> 00:21:09,334
To keep a collection among
his wine…

224
00:21:09,400 --> 00:21:11,334
So who do you suppose was
the caller?

225
00:21:11,400 --> 00:21:13,966
It really couldn't have been
the dead.

226
00:21:16,633 --> 00:21:18,333
It's so strange.

227
00:21:23,666 --> 00:21:26,933
Don't lend your bodies to
spirits so recklessly like that.

228
00:21:28,000 --> 00:21:29,400
Promise me,

229
00:21:29,466 --> 00:21:32,200
